{:cap/id :cap/voice-synth
 :cap/tools [
             ;; :voice.openutau_project
             :voice.tts
             :voice.tts_stream
             :bash]
 :cap/description
  "Spoken and sung voice synthesis. Current Voxx API contract:
   - Sung: voice.openutau_project scaffolds a .ustx file for OpenUtau render.
   - Spoken TTS: voice.tts calls the Voxx gateway via the OpenAI-compatible
      /v1/audio/speech API shape (mp3 by default); shell workflows may use
      ~/.pi/agent/skills/voice-tts/tts.sh.
      voice.tts_stream connects to the knoxx WS bridge at /ws/voice/tts.
   - Per-request provider selection: use voice.tts model_id or tts.sh --model with
      kokoro, melo, espeak, xiaomi_mimo, requesty, or openai; confirm the actual
      renderer with Voxx's x-openhax-tts-backend header when debugging.
   - Per-request postprocess: use --postprocess-profile sports|broadcast|narrator|radio|soft,
      --postprocess off for dry capture, or the REST query/json fields postprocess_profile,
      postprocess, and postprocess_enabled.
   - Prompt-aware inflection tags: use --prompt-aware and optional --prompt-aware-style to ask
      capable providers to treat tags like [excited], [whisper], [pause], or <break time=\"500ms\" />
      as performance directions instead of spoken text. This is provider-dependent.
   - Provider resilience: if a remote backend (for example Xiaomi MiMo) returns quota, rate-limit, auth,
      or status-code errors, do not rewrite prompts or bypass Voxx. Keep local fallbacks after it in
      VOICE_GATEWAY_TTS_BACKEND_ORDER, e.g. xiaomi_mimo,kokoro,melo,espeak or kokoro,melo,espeak.
   - Queue safety: Voxx has a bounded processing queue; on queue-full or timeout responses, back off
      instead of launching parallel retries.
   - Pitch processing: capture dry TTS with --postprocess off, then chain through
      ~/.pi/agent/skills/autotune/ (rubberband + sox pipeline, skill:autotune).
   Auth: reads VOXX_URL and VOICE_GATEWAY_API_KEY.
   Default voice: alloy. Default model: kokoro. Default postprocess: sports-commentator-v1.
   Prefer Voxx for backend-agnostic synthesis (Kokoro first; optional Xiaomi MiMo/Requesty/OpenAI; MeloTTS/eSpeak fallback). Do not wire direct ElevenLabs."
 :cap/skills [:skill/voice-tts :skill/autotune]
 :cap/user-surfaces [{:surface/id :workspace/voice-synth
                      :surface/label "Voice synthesis workbench"
                      :surface/kind :composer
                      :surface/routes ["/ops/documents"]
                      :surface/description
                       "Spoken TTS via the Voxx gateway (REST + WS streaming), per-request postprocess profiles,
                        prompt-aware performance tags for capable providers, sung synthesis via OpenUtau, and
                        pitch processing via rubberband/sox autotune pipeline."}]}
